<subSubSection id="89FA97953A03FFE370A7E8284E44D5AA" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="27" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="C15FC41E3A03FFE070A7E8284C6BD29F" blockId="1.[151,1436,1848,2029]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="F394180C3A03FFE070A7E8284D76D220" bold="true" box="[198,556,1848,1874]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Distribution and ecology:—</emphasis>
Known so far only from the Guianas, but in view of its occurrence in secondary habitats, the species is probably more widespread. Perhaps it was once reported as 
<taxonomicName id="06E0BF9D3A03FFE0757FE84F4ED4D2D2" authority="S. Stenroos (1989: 252)" authorityName="S. Stenroos" authorityPageNumber="252" authorityYear="1989" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Cladoniaceae" genus="Cladonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ahtii">
<emphasis id="F394180C3A03FFE0757FE84F4A20D20A" box="[1310,1402,1887,1912]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">C. ahtii</emphasis>
S. 
<bibRefCitation id="A571B9EF3A03FFE070F6E8964ED4D2D2" author="Stenroos, S." box="[151,398,1926,1952]" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" pagination="237 - 261" refId="ref7246" refString="Stenroos, S. (1989) Taxonomic revision of the Cladonia miniata group. Annales Botanici Fennici 26: 237 - 261." type="journal article" year="1989">Stenroos (1989: 252)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from adjacent 
<collectingCountry id="B9F7848E3A03FFE07221E8964DE1D2D2" box="[576,699,1926,1952]" name="Venezuela" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, in 
<collectingRegion id="03240AFC3A03FFE07284E8964C67D2D2" box="[741,829,1926,1952]" country="Venezuela" name="Bolivar" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">Bolívar</collectingRegion>
near Canaima, epiphytic at 
<quantity id="061869FB3A03FFE074E6E8964B88D2D2" box="[1159,1234,1926,1952]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" unit="m" value="550.0">550 m</quantity>
elev.; this record was excluded from 
<taxonomicName id="06E0BF9D3A03FFE071E3E8BD4E81D2B4" authorityName="S. Stenroos" authorityYear="1989" box="[386,475,1965,1990]" class="Lecanoromycetes" family="Cladoniaceae" genus="Cladonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Lecanorales" pageId="1" pageNumber="26" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ahtii">
<emphasis id="F394180C3A03FFE071E3E8BD4E81D2B4" box="[386,475,1965,1990]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="26">C. ahtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Ahti (2000). The species was found exclusively epiphytic on hepatic film on smooth, living palm stems in plantations along the coast.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C15FC41E3A00FFE370A7EF874E44D5AA" blockId="2.[151,1439,151,719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="27">
